found social, economic, and cultural change as the result of a long process of integration into the British Atlantic world. A transatlantic perspective, therefore, undergirds this biography, from an exploration of how Holmes’s family members were participants in an Atlantic world of trade and consumption, to explaining how his educational experiences at Edinburgh and Paris informed his approach to the practice of medicine, medical education, and medical politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aAnglicanszQuébec (Province)zMontréalvBiography. 0aAnglicanszQuébec (Province)zMontréalvBiography. 0aDeans (Education)zQuébec (Province)zMontréalvBiography. 0aDeans (Education)zQuébec (Province)zMontréalvBiography. 0aMedical teaching personnelzQuébec (Province)zMontréalvBiography. 0aMedical teaching personnelzQuébec (Province)zMontréalvBiography. 0aPhysicianszQuébec (Province)zMontréalvBiography. 0aPhysicianszQuébec (Province)zMontréalvBiography. 0aPhysicians. 7aHISTORY / Canada / General.2bisacsh  aAndrew Fernando Holmes.  aHolmes’s heart.  aMaude Abbott.  aNatural History Society of Montreal.  aProtestant evangelicalism in Quebec.  aQuebec.  aorigins of McGill medicine.  apolitics of medicine in Lower Canada.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z97831106904530 cprintz978148750219540uhttps://d